The Council shall consist of the following members:
The Governor or the Governor's designee;
The Secretary of Higher Education;
The Secretary of Labor, Licensing, and Regulation;
The Secretary of Business and Economic Development;
The Chancellor of the University System of Maryland;
The State Superintendent of Schools;
The Chairman of the Maryland Higher Education Commission;
The Chair and the Executive Director of the Governor's Workforce Investment Board;
Two members of the House of Delegates, appointed by the Speaker of the House;
Two members of the Senate of Maryland, appointed by the President of the Senate; and
The following members appointed by the Governor:
A member of the State Board of Education;
A representative of local superintendents of education;
A representative of local boards of education;
Two members of employee organizations that represent elementary and secondary school personnel in the State;
A representative of elementary and secondary school principals;
Two representatives of nonpublic elementary and secondary schools;
An expert in early childhood education;
An expert in career and technology education;
Two representatives of community colleges;
Two representatives of independent colleges or universities;
A representative of public institutions of higher education outside the University System of Maryland;
A representative of college or university deans who has responsibility for a science, technology, engineering, and math (STEM) discipline;
Four representatives of the University System of Maryland;
A representative of a for-profit institution of higher education;
Three representatives of the business community; and
Six additional members with experience and knowledge that will benefit the work of the Council.

section.section:
The Executive Committee shall include the following members:
The Governor or the Governor's designee;
The Secretary of Higher Education;
The Secretary of Labor, Licensing, and Regulation;
The Secretary of Business and Economic Development;
The Chancellor of the University System of Maryland; and
The State Superintendent of Schools.

text.section:
The Council shall investigate ways to improve education, advance workforce creation, and make the State more competitive through some or all of the following strategies:
Ensuring that all students have the basic, critical thinking, and technical skills necessary to succeed in the modern workplace;
Reducing dropout rates and increasing retention and graduation rates in high school and college;
Improving student achievement and closing student achievement gaps;
Improving teaching quality;
Improving teacher retention;
Strengthening and expanding educational leadership programs;
Redesigning career and technology education programs to meet college expectations and employer needs;
Expanding the availability of career and technology programs and high school centers;
Strengthening STEM programs at the high school and college levels;
Connecting high school expectations and college expectations with employer needs;
Creating pathways for all students to obtain college degrees;
Providing teachers the resources and professional training they need to help students reach higher standards;
Expanding opportunities for continuous learning;
Aligning high school graduation requirements with college readiness requirements;
Improving the connections between the pre-kindergarten, primary, secondary, and higher education systems;
Creating programs and incentives to encourage mutually beneficial relationships between schools, school systems, higher education, and the business community; and
Any other strategies requested by the Governor or General Assembly.
